723155f-b.title: Manhattan: St. Nicholas Avenue - 169th Street (West)
723155f-b.text:
(1)
St. Nicholas Ave., east side, south from West 169th Street, show-
ing low structures lining a triangular area caused by the convergence
of Broadway and the above Ave., and is known as Mitchell Square.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
A detail of same, showing mainly the N.E. corner of West 169th
Street. Occupying the balance of this block and facing on the west
side of Audubon Ave. is P.S. 169, the rear of which appears on the
right.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
